----------
Translator
----------

Dependencies:
  ghc; cmdargs; executable-path; Java >= 5 (only for compiling XsdCheck.java)

To install GHC refer to:
  http://www.haskell.org/ghc/distribution_packages

Install monad transformer library (Ubuntu):
  sudo apt-get install libghc-mtl-dev

To install cmdargs execute:
  cabal install cmdargs
  cabal install executable-path

If you have no cabal then installt it (Ubuntu):
  sudo apt-get install cabal-install
  cabal update

Once the libraries are in place, compile the translator:
  make

Usage:  
   clafer <filename>.cfr
   
   by default, the translator produces Alloy 4 output. Use
   -m=xml 		to produce XML output
   -m=clafer 	to produce desugared Clafer output
   -m=alloy42 	to produce Alloy 4.2 output

---------
Validator
---------
The translator can validate its XML, Alloy 4 and 4.2, and Clafer output.

Dependencies:
   Java >= 5; XsdCheck.class and Alloy binaries (alloy4.jar and/or alloy4.2-rc.jar) are placed in <clafer installation folder>/Test/tools.

Usage:
   -v 		to invoke the validator for the given kind of output